main thing in terms of a different choice is that i 
wish i had gotten some blow my camera somebody else

11:00.738 --> 11:28.922
get a picture of me standing in front of the the 
statute, the Gossett democracy. I was going to

11:30.737 --> 11:35.023
have all three of us, myself and our two kids, do 
that. Of course, now that opportunity is gone.

11:44.215 --> 11:47.259
Some people ask, why didn't you go back down to the 
square? Why didn't you try to see what was going on?

11:49.181 --> 11:53.908
And I realized that that would be a very foolish 
thing to do. And I still think that I made the right

11:53.988 --> 11:57.232
decision. Once the violence broke out, I realized 
even though it was not directed towards

11:59.260 --> 12:08.970
foreigners, if I just happened to be in the wrong 
place at the wrong time, they were going to stop

11:59.260 --> 12:08.970
shooting because, oh, there goes a foreigner. We 
don't want to shoot him. So I think that I made the

12:11.152 --> 12:17.159
right decision there. OK. And then lastly, you 
shared about the camera. So you had that as visual

12:21.523 --> 12:26.488
images of where you had been. When you got back to 
College Station, I know you had shared with me an

12:29.433 --> 12:35.240
article you wrote called China's Pro-Democracy 
Movement. Did you make any other written records

12:35.821 --> 12:41.869
or journal accounts? Well, when I got back, I was 
one of the first Americans who'd been to Tiananmen

12:42.349 --> 12:47.736
Square and who had come back. So a lot of the news 
media was interested in hearing what I had to say.

12:55.306 --> 13:02.957
One of the TV stations in Houston was at the airport 
when I got there, and I had a radio station in that

12:55.306 --> 13:02.957
calling. And it

13:03.979 --> 13:17.598
upset me in that the main thing they were 
interested in was how many bodies did you see, a

13:03.979 --> 13:17.598
body count, and how much blood was there. Not 
really in terms of what was going on, what was the

13:18.219 --> 13:23.166
significance of this thing, and what was really 
happening. Of

13:24.293 --> 13:31.400
course, my body clock, my biological clock was 
off. I got back here Wednesday, and Thursday

13:31.781 --> 13:53.963
morning, I guess about 3 o'clock in the morning, I 
was, I woke up and couldn't go back to sleep, and so I

13:31.781 --> 13:53.963
went into my den and wrote up a short article that 
was later printed by several papers in Houston and

13:54.297 --> 14:04.372
San Antonio and Austin, around the state and some 
other states, kind of pulling together in a

13:54.297 --> 14:04.372
relatively short form of what I had seen. And then 
over the summer, because I'd given some talks in

14:05.093 --> 14:21.638
that and found out more, kind of tried to make some 
sense for myself as to what I was going on, what had

14:05.093 --> 14:21.638
happened, what led up to the demonstration of what 
happened there and what was going on in China over

14:22.023 --> 14:28.012
the summer. And then I ended up with the six-page 
paper that I sent you. But newspapers aren't

14:36.825 --> 14:50.646
arrested in things that are that long or that 
detailed, so it's more for personal use in

14:36.825 --> 14:50.646
reminding me and giving to friends who were 
arrested, you know, what was really happening,

14:36.825 --> 14:50.646
what was going on. When you say the newspapers, for 
example, did the local newspaper here in College

14:51.368 --> 15:05.504
Station interested in your work, or was it only... 
Yeah, both the local newspaper and the local TV

14:51.368 --> 15:05.504
station, they came out. Again, the first question 
was, you know, how many bodies did you see, how many

15:06.185 --> 15:10.129
people did you see killed? And even though I told 
them that I did not see anybody killed on that,

15:11.070 --> 15:21.021
still in the newspaper article, There was some 
mention that I'd seen some people shot. I want to

15:26.116 --> 15:27.578
give them the benefit of the doubt. They tried the 
best they could to take a relatively long

15:27.618 --> 15:38.367
interview and get the gist of what was going on. But 
I guess they think they've got to make it

15:39.448 --> 15:49.017
interesting to the viewers and the readers, so 
they've got to get some of that type of stuff in

15:39.448 --> 15:49.017
there. I wouldn't give them the doubt. It was an 
honest effort, honest mistake. They weren't

15:54.174 --> 16:01.501
deliberately trying to twist what I had said into 
something that I hadn't. Lastly, one last

16:01.521 --> 16:08.508
question in terms of do you hope to go back to China 
any time in the near future? If the opportunity

16:08.528 --> 16:12.211
arises, I would love to be able to go back. As long as 
the current regime is in, I don't know if they will

16:13.092 --> 16:16.896
let me go back. I've been rather vocal about what I 
saw. I felt that was something that I owed to the

16:19.838 --> 16:25.324
people in Tiananmen Square. And like I said, there 
were more people who were killed outside of the

16:25.364 --> 16:29.970
square than were killed in the square. I'm 
convinced that the accurate count is more around

16:31.512 --> 16:48.332
2,000 or 3,000 than what some people are putting 
around as a couple of hundred, to let the world know

16:31.512 --> 16:48.332
what happened in the square. if I apply for a visa, 
the Chinese government might not let me go back.

16:51.759 --> 16:56.285
But if they do, I think I would be, it would be safe. I 
don't think they're going to haul me off and throw

16:56.345 --> 17:01.051
me in jail if they let me go back. Of course, I'd have 
to be very careful about what I said and what I did

17:01.612 --> 17:08.060
while I was there, but I would not give them any 
excuse. And I said, if the modern element gains

17:08.080 --> 17:18.133
control after Deng Xiaoping's death and 
continues the reforms and opening up, I think it

17:18.687 --> 17:19.868
would be safe. And I would like to go back and be able 
to see what changes have taken place. And I know my

17:27.378 --> 17:37.090
two older kids were really disappointed that they 
didn't get to go and want to go back there. So if an

17:37.130 --> 17:39.814
opportunity arises, we'll try to get there. You 
would consider going back with the family? Oh,

17:42.437 --> 17:42.697
yeah. Oh, yeah. OK. Thank you very much for sharing 
with us today about your in China at a time that were

17:48.185 --> 17:57.401
very volatile, but of which the Western world is 
very interested in knowing about. Thank you

17:57.441 --> 17:58.465
again.

